   VILNIUS
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Visiting French President Francois Mitterrand yesterday called the continued
presence of former Soviet troops in Lithuania 'abnormal and shocking',
Reuter reports from Vilnius.
Mr Mitterrand, the most senior western leader to visit the Baltic states
since they regained independence from Moscow last August, told the
