FT  15 MAY 92 / Complaints against police increase
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
THE Police Complaints Authority handled 7,953 cases last year, a rise of 9
per cent on the previous year, although serious cases fell by 15 per cent to
4,330.
The most common complaints were of assault, incivility, irregular procedures
and neglect of duty. One in 10 cases led to action being taken.
