<HEADLINE>
FT  15 MAY 92 / Charges allege Pounds 1.3m fraud
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
MR Malcolm Johnson, a businessman, appeared before City of London
magistrates yesterday charged with eight counts of fraud involving more than
Dollars 2.4m (Pounds 1.3m). It followed his extradition from Austria on
Wednesday after a request by the Serious Fraud Office.
The charges against him include obtaining Dollars 2.4m by deception from
Postel Investment Management by purporting that shares in Duralite
Manufacturing were shares in a properly constituted company with assets of
over Dollars 20m.
Mr Johnson, 43, of Betchworth, Surrey, was remanded on conditional bail
until July 9.
