<HEADLINE>
FT  15 MAY 92 / Pay deal for NHS blue-collar staff
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
NATIONAL Health Service blue-collar workers have accepted an offer worth 4.9
per cent on the pay bill.
The 180,000 workers, who include domestics, porters and catering and laundry
staff, will have their increase backdated to April 1. The lowest-paid will
receive increases of up to 6.7 per cent.
The settlement is consistent with a recent pay increase for white-collar NHS
workers but below the average of 6.5 per cent awarded to doctors and nurses
after pay-review recommendations earlier this year.
</TEXT>
