<HEADLINE>
FT  15 MAY 92 / Banknote theft probed by police
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
EIGHT people have been arrested by police investigating the alleged theft of
money from the Bank of England's depot at Debden, Essex, where old banknotes
are destroyed.
Scotland Yard said a large quantity of cash had been recovered but did not
reveal the amount.
The arrests by officers of the Company Fraud Squad and No 9 Regional Crime
Squad were made yesterday at three addresses in Loughton and one at
Chelmsford, Essex. The four men and four women arrested were released on
police bail pending further inquiries.
Neither the police nor the Bank would confirm a report in today's Daily Mail
that up to Pounds 50m may have been stolen from the depot.
