FT  15 MAY 92 / UK Company News: Property sale lifts Finlay to Pounds 10.8m
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Helped by a surplus on sale of property, James Finlay, the overseas trading
and financial services group, increased pre-tax profits from Pounds 9.52m to
Pounds 10.8m in 1991.
Turnover slipped to Pounds 144m (Pounds 149m) but the operating surplus rose
to Pounds 12.8m (Pounds 11.1m) with the help of a Pounds 1.3m profit from
the sale of property by George Payne.
Contribution from plantations was held at Pounds 4.34m, confectionery and
beverage provided Pounds 6.57m (Pounds 4.56m) including the property deal,
