3.15m), property accounted for Pounds 369,000 (Pounds 343,000), and oil and
gas interests showed a deficit of Pounds 75,000 (surplus Pounds 324,000).
Geographically, the two biggest contributors were the UK and Africa with
Pounds 7.08m (Pounds 4.54m) and Pounds 5.08m (Pounds 3.77m) respectively.
North America fell behind at Pounds 985,000 (Pounds 2.53m) as did Asia with
Pounds 344,000 (Pounds 1.6m), but Australasia cut its loss to Pounds 645,000
(Pounds 1.36m).
Earnings per share were 6.8p (6p) and the dividend is held at 4.15p with a
second interim of 2.15p.
