<HEADLINE>
FT  15 MAY 92 / UK Company News: John Foster cuts loss to Pounds 381,000
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
With the inclusion of exceptional credits John Foster &amp; Son, the specialist
textile group, made substantial inroads into its losses in the year to
February 28.
Trading conditions remained depressed, with the resultant intense
competition for business. Turnover fell to Pounds 22.7m (Pounds 26.6m) but
the operating deficit was reduced to Pounds 1.4m (Pounds 1.56m); taking in
credits of Pounds 1.02m (debits Pounds 676,000) left the year's pre-tax loss
at Pounds 381,000 (Pounds 2.24m).
Losses per share were 2.3p (14p) after tax credits of Pounds 131,000 (Pounds
678,000). The dividend is again 0.5p.
Mr David Allen, managing director, reported that the balance sheet was
strong, new products and designs had been well received and, despite two
difficult years, the group was in good shape.
