<HEADLINE>
FT  15 MAY 92 / Technology (Worth Watching): Insect repellent goes tree
climbing
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PAUL TAYLOR
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Climbing insects, such as ants, can devastate a fruit crop. But an
environmentally friendly device which claims to give nearly 100 per cent
protection has been developed by Oecos, a Hertfordshire-based company.
The device consists of a 20mm thick foam trapping strip which compresses and
moulds to the contours of the tree trunk. This is covered by a green
UV-degradable band to protect it from debris and keep it out of reach of
hungry birds. It is effective against winter moths, aphids, earwigs and
spider mites. Oecos: UK, 0438 832481.
</TEXT>
