<HEADLINE>
FT  15 MAY 92 / Spain's inflationary pressures ease
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PETER BRUCE
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   MADRID
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
SPAIN'S cost of living index rose just 0.2 per cent in April marking the
first slowdown in inflationary pressure this year, writes Peter Bruce in
Madrid. Year-on-year inflation fell from 6.9 per cent to 6.5 per cent - the
start, according to the finance ministry, of a gradual approach to its
inflation estimate for the year of 5.8 per cent. That would still be a rise
on the 5.5 per cent recorded in 1991 but there have been sharp VAT increases
in the first quarter of this year.  Despite the good April figures, however,
underlying inflation (which excludes energy and processed food prices) is
still high at 6.8 per cent.
</TEXT>
