<HEADLINE>
FT  15 MAY 92 / Survey: FT Traveller, Genoa (11) - Key facts for the
business visitor
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Telephones
Genoa dialing code 010 from inside Italy. For callers from outside Italy
country code is 39, then 10 for Genoa.
Hotels
City centre hotels can get very full during big trade fairs, notably the
October boat show, and visitors are advised to book well in advance.
Starhotel President, corte Lambruschini 4; Tel: 5727; Rates: single
L265,000-310,000, double L310.000-385,000.
Bristol, via 20 Settembre 35; Tel: 592541; Rates: single L210,000, double
L300,000.
Jolly Plaza, via Martin Piaggio 11; Tel: 8393641; Rates: single L210,000,
double L290,000.
Savoia Majestic, via Arsenale di Terra 5; Tel: 261641; Rates: single
L195,000, double L280,000.
City, via San Sebastiano 6: Tel: 5545; Rates: single L170,000, double
L240,000.
Restaurants
Saint Cyr, piazza Marsala 8; Tel: 886897. Behind the Jolly hotel, elegant
surroundings and fine local food, notably fish. L80,000-L100,000 a head with
wine.
Gran Gotto, via Fiume 11; Tel: 564344. Attractive ambience near the Corte
Lambruschini complex and piazza della Vittorio. Local Ligurian specialities,
especially fish. Around L80,000 a head with wine.
Primo Piano, via 20 Settembre 36; Tel: 540284. Stylish first floor
restaurant which cultivates a clubbish style, with views over the arcardes
of one of Genoa's main shopping streets. L80,000-100,000 a head with wine.
Clubs
Genoa has a handful of exclusive clubs. Though closed to non-members, they
are worth viewing, and ideal for discreet corporate entertaining for those
with membership.
Circolo Artistico del Tunnel, via Garibaldi 5; Tel: 280379. Genoa's most
famous and exclusive club. Its name is believed to be drawn from the opening
of a new rail tunnel between the city and Sampierdarena in 1875, the year of
its founding. Membership limited to 500.
Il Santa Caterina, salita Santa Caterina 8; Tel: 5533119. Small but
beautifully-restored premises in an ancient Palazzo close to via Garibaldi.
A new club, principally for dining, which is trying to compete with its
established counterparts.
Yachting Club, porticciolo duca Abruzzi; Tel: 293865. As its name implies,
Genoa's leading sailing club. Also exclusive.
Culture
The new Carlo Fenice Opera House is the city's cultural showcase for opera
and classical music. Tickets are still hard to come by, as the building
retains strong curiosity value for locals. Piazza De Ferrari. Box office,
Tel: 589329 or 5704067.
Teatro della Corte and Teatro Genovese are the city's two main theatres for
drama. The former is part of the new Corte Lambruschini complex while the
latter is more traditional in its design. Box office: Teatro della Corte,
Piazza Borgo Pila 42, Tel: 5702450; Teatro Genovese, via Martin Piaggio 4,
Tel: 8393589.
Airport
Christoforo Colombo airport, Tel: 2411, flight information 2415410, is four
miles west of the city and has regular Alitalia and ATi flights to most big
Italian cities. There are also connections to many European centres with
flights by British Airways and others. Buses from town leave for the airport
from Piazza Verdi and piazza Acquaverde.
Airlines
Alitalia, via XII Ottobre 188, Tel: 54938. Air France, via XII Ottobre 2,
Tel: 594710. British Airways, via E. Vernazza 23, Tel: 2415238. Lufthansa,
via E. Vernazza 23, Tel: 605902. KLM, via Fieschi 2, Tel: 586471. Olympic,
via XII Ottobre 2, Tel: 541068. Swissair, via E. Vernazza 23, Tel: 542841.
Media
Genoa's daily newspaper is the established Il Secolo XIX, edited near
Brignole station and owned by the Perrone family. All main national papers
are found first thing in the morning, and some have a separate Genoa
supplement. Foreign papers such as the Financial Times are widely available,
but seldom arrive before mid-afternoon.
Tourist information
Main office (from tomorrow) via Roma 11. Tel: 541541. Other branches at
Piazza Verdi 18/R (by Brignole station) Tel: 583398; Principe station Tel:
262633. There is also an office at the airport, Tel: 2415247. Open 8am-8pm.
Closed Sundays.
The province of Genoa also has its own tourist information office at via
Roma 11. Tel: 581375 or 581407.
Trade fairs
The Fiera di Genova is at piazzale Kennedy 1, Tel: 53911. Main functions are
Autostory (vintage cars) Jan 24-Feb 2. AF - The Automated Factory show Feb
17-21. Primavera (general spring fair) March 27-April 5. Riabitat (building
renovation &amp; maintenance) May 27-31. Boat Show Oct 17-25. Tecnhotel (items
for hotel business) Nov 19-23.
Chambers of Commerce
Chamber of Commerce, via Garibaldi 4. Tel: 207989. National Institute of
Foreign Trade, via Ravasco 10. Tel: 566596. Union of Chambers of Commerce of
Liguria, via San Lorenzo 15. Tel: 204448. Genova Chamber of Commerce of
Industry, Handiwork and Agriculture, via Garibaldi 4, Tel: 20941.
Consulates
As a leading port, Genoa has consular representation for 50 countries.
Addresses for the most important are:
Belgium, via Interiano 3, Tel: 589692.
Denmark, via San Siro 10, Tel: 297453.
France, via Garibaldi 20, Tel: 200879.
Germany, via San Vincenzo 4, Tel: 546457.
Greece, Porta Vittoria 12, Tel: 564416.
Netherlands, via XII Ottobre 2, Tel: 566838.
Portugal, via Assarotti 17/A, Tel: 870212.
Russia, via Ghirardelli Pescetto 16, Tel: 326047.
Spain, via Brig Liguria 3, Tel: 587177.
Sweden, via Porta Varagine 1, Tel: 293583.
Switzerland, via Porta Brignole 3, Tel: 565620.
UK, via XII Ottobre 2, Tel: 5531510.
US, via Porta Portello 6, Tel: 282741.
Sport
Football: L Ferraris Stadium, 39,950 seats. One kilometre from the city
centre. Tickets available on Tuesday before a football match ranging from
L25,000 to L120,000. Genoa Point, Tel: 589012; Solo Sampdoria, Tel: 589012.
Golf: Golf Rapallo, Tel: 0185 50210, closed on Tuesdays; Golf Club Arenzano,
Tel: 9111817, closed Tuesdays and during October.
Swimming: Stadio del Nuoto - Albaro, Tel: 3628409, open Mondays to Fridays.
Open Saturdays depending on sporting events.
Tennis: Stadio tennis, Tel: 317604; Park Tennis Club (for members only),
Tel: 312492.
Useful numbers:
General events: CONI (National Olympic Committee) Tel: 581682; CSI (Italian
Sporting Centre) Tel: 208917.
Athletics: Federazione Atletica Leggera, Tel: 884349.
Baseball/softball: federazione Baseball e Softball, Tel: 889593
Basketball: Federazione Pallacanestro, Tel: 870858.
Cycling: Federazione Ciclistica Italiana, Tel: 882415.
Fishing and diving: Federazione Pesca e Att. Subacquee, Tel: 587730.
Flying club: Aeroclub d'Italia, Tel: 6512727.
Football: Federazione Italiana Calcio, Tel: 891482.
Gymnastics: Federazione Ginnastica Italiana, Tel: 889915.
Riding: Federazione It Sport Equestri, Tel: 870333.
Rowing: Rowing Club Genova, Tel: 204772.
Rugby: Federazione Italiana Rugby, Tel: 562513.
Sailing: Federazione Italiana Vela, Tel: 565723; Lega Navale Italiana, Tel:
542067; Yacht Club Italiano, Tel: 293865.
Swimming: Federazione Italiana Nuoto, Tel: 311298.
Tennis: Federazione Italiana Tennis, Tel: 543298.
