FT  14 MAY 92 / International Company News: Equitable flotation scheme
approved
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By NIKKI TAIT
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
THE New York State Insurance Department has given the go-ahead for the
demutualisation scheme at The Equitable Life Assurance Society, the large US
life insurer.
This is by far the largest demutualisation - the process whereby a mutual
insurer, controlled by its policyholders, turns itself into a 'conventional'
shareholder-owned company - to take place in the US. Equitable policyholders
have already approved the move.
The next step in the process will be the flotation of Equitable shares on
the stock market, an event scheduled for this summer. Once that is complete,
Axa, the French insurance group, should emerge with a 40-49 per cent stake
in Equitable in return for its Dollars 1bn infusion of capital into the
ailing US group last year.
