<HEADLINE>
FT  14 MAY 92 / International Company News: Pearlstine to resign from Dow
Jones
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ALAN FRIEDMAN
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
MR NORMAN PEARLSTINE, executive editor of The Wall Street Journal and the
man who launched the newspaper's European edition 10 years ago, is resigning
from Dow Jones, the media group that owns The Journal, to start his own
media company.
Mr Pearlstine, 49, joined Dow Jones in 1968 as a reporter in The Journal's
Dallas bureau, and in 1976 became the first managing editor of The Asian
Wall Street Journal, based in Hong Kong.
In 1983, after directing the launch of the paper's European edition, Mr
Pearlstine returned to New York to become a vice-president of The Journal
and managing editor of the US edition.
Last year he was named executive editor and took on responsibilities such as
the launch of SmartMoney, a personal business magazine that is a joint
venture between Dow Jones and the Hearst group.
Mr Pearlstine will leave Dow Jones on June 30, but he will remain a
consultant to SmartMoney and to Dow Jones on book and television projects in
which he has been involved.
Mr Paul Steiger, who became managing editor of The Journal in 1991, will
take responsibility for The Journal's news department.
Mr Peter Kann, chairman of Dow Jones, said he regretted Mr Pearlstine's
decision to resign, but that 'the entrepreneur in any of us' could
understand it.
</TEXT>
