<TEXT>
BBC SELECT, the subscription television service of the BBC, may launch
family educational programmes including language tuition for children. A
pilot programme on French for children aged seven to 11 has been produced,
and talks on collaboration have started with publishers.
Ms Angie Mason, senior commissioning editor for education at BBC Select,
said: 'It's a question of which publishers we decide to go with.'
She was speaking after the official launch of BBC Select, which plans to use
