FT  14 MAY 92 / Ministers review London bus plans
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By RICHARD TOMKINS, Transport Correspondent
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
CONTROVERSIAL proposals for the deregulation and privatisation of the London
bus network appear to be undergoing a review by the fresh ministerial team
at the Department of Transport.
The department yesterday announced that a working party comprising a range
of interests in the capital had been set up 'to advise on the practical
aspects of implementing deregulation.'
Mr Steven Norris, minister for transport in London, said the government
remained committed to extending bus de-regulation to the capital.
However, the creation of the working party follows last week's surprise
omission from the Queen's Speech of legislative proposals for London bus
deregulation, which previous transport minsters had consistently promised
early in the next parliament.
Transport ministers seem unlikely to drop deregulation altogether, but some
Conservative MPs in the capital are believed to be deeply concerned about
the proposals in their present form.
