<HEADLINE>
FT  14 MAY 92 / Italy's presidential election begins with scuffles
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Italy's presidential election began with scuffles yesterday when neo-fascist
MPs, shouting 'thieves', tried to storm the benches of Italy's largest
party, the ruling Christian Democrats. Members of parliament traded blows
before voting began. Against the background of a bribery scandal which has
hit all the main parties, 1,014 electors drawn from the two parliamentary
chambers and Italy's 20 regions must choose a new head of state before a new
government can be formed. A result is not expected before Friday night.
Brawl adds to drama, Page 2
</TEXT>
