<HEADLINE>
FT  14 MAY 92 / World Stock Markets: South Africa
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
CONTINUED demand for quality shares and a lack of sellers pushed leading
shares off their lows to close firmer in thin trade. The overall index rose
9 to 3,642 and the industrial index gained 5 to 4,534. The gold index added
3 to 1,070.
</TEXT>
